subSubSection.paragraph:
Operculum
(
Figs 29, 30
, 
38
). Very large (5.0–6.6 mm in diameter) in relation to body width, cylindrical, multispiral, tightly fitting inside shell tube; composed of numerous spiral layers of corneous lamellae, the earlier ones usually decollate and only 8–12 remaining attached to the animal (height of operculum then 6.8– 
12 mm
). Edge of each layer with flat spine-like projections (
Fig. 30
); lamella not continuous internally: core filled with triangular compartments, about 6 per whorl, spirally arranged around a central axis (
Fig. 29
).
